author: Elle Halliwell
title: Jesinta Campbell says she regrets her Miss Universe hair and makeup decisions |
text:
JESINTA Campbell wishes she could forget the multitudes of makeup, hair and fashion crimes she committed during her Miss Universe Australia reign.
The 24-year-old, who rarely puts a step wrong nowadays when it comes to her grooming and style, made the admission yesterday to Sydney Confidential.
“I think I regret every hair choice, make up choice and fashion choice I made in 2010 as Miss Universe Australia,” the fiance of AFL player Buddy Franklin said, laughing.
“You just may as well block that part out of my life and just pretend it never happened.”
Jesinta Campbell. Source: News Limited
Jesinta during her early modelling days. Source: News Limited
Campbell, who has reprised her ambassador role for Joico’s Christmas Joi of Giving campaign with the Starlight Foundation, said her hair was still recovering from the damage done by the endless hair extensions.
“The whole thing was just so tacky, and the hair extensions, that’s why my hair’s short now because it’s still recovering from how many extensions I had in during my reign,” she said
Jesinta Campbell, Miss Australia 2010, poses for in her national costume at the Mandalay Bay Resort and Casino in Las Vegas August 16, 2010. Picture: Matt Petit/AP. Source: News Limited
The Getaway presenter said she was looking forward to enjoying some family time this Christmas with Franklin and their families. “It will either be at our home in Sydney or up at the Gold Coast,” she said.
“We’ll both have a bit of time off, I did the David Jones Boxing Day sales last Christmas so I was in bed at eight o’clock … so I’m looking forward to not having to work Boxing Day.”
Model Jesinta Campbell is looking forward to a work free Christmas this year. Source: News Corp Australia
 ‘I regret hair, makeup, fashion choices’
